<!-- Programs Layout -->
<section class="py-8 px-3 px-sm-4 px-md-5" style="  margin-top: 88px; min-height: calc(100vh - 88px);">
    <div class="max-width-1200 mx-auto">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="mb-4">
        <h2 class="fw-bold">Purposeful learning for every age.</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="row">




        




<div class="col-lg-8">

  <!-- Workshops & Classes -->
  <div class="card mb-5 p-4 border-yellow">
    <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-4">
      <h4 class="mb-0">Workshops and Classes</h4>
      <p class="lead mb-0">Engaging sessions that blend rigorous academics with the joy of play. Learners of diverse ages come together to explore ideas, build projects, and collaborate in a supportive environment.</p>
      <p class="mb-0">Workshops are typically 1 hour long and offer quick, high-energy explorations.<br> Classes run 45 to 90 minutes and occur one to two times per week for deeper study. <br> Sessions are scheduled on weekday afternoons and evenings to fit family routines.</p>
      <p class="mb-0">Instruction is learner-led and inquiry-driven, guided by credentialed teachers who document growth and reflect with learners and families. Expect a mix of STEAM investigations, creative thinking, and authentic communication practice woven into meaningful, real-world contexts.</p>
      <p class="mb-0"><strong>Outcomes:</strong> confidence in problem-solving, stronger communication and social-emotional skills, and a lasting curiosity that transfers beyond the classroom.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Field Trips -->
  <div class="card mb-5 p-4 border-purple">
    <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-4">
      <h4 class="mb-0">Field Trips</h4>
      <p class="lead mb-0">Personalized experiences that connect learning to the community. Trips are designed around each learner’s interests and needs, with intentional guidance for social, emotional, and behavioral growth.</p>
      <p class="mb-0">Experiences may be solo, with a buddy, or in a small group, and range from focused outings to half-day explorations. Destinations include cultural, scientific, and nature-based settings that invite hands-on discovery and conversation.</p>
      <p class="mb-0"><strong>Outcomes:</strong> increased independence, situational awareness, and a deeper sense of belonging in public spaces—plus plenty of real-world practice with planning, flexibility, and reflection.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Vocational & Service Learning -->
  <div class="card mb-5 p-4 border-blue">
    <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-4">
      <h4 class="mb-0">Vocational Opportunities & Service Learning</h4>
      <p class="lead mb-0">Purpose-driven, hands-on learning that turns interests into experience. Internships and apprenticeships for teens and young adults provide structured pathways to contribute, practice, and grow.</p>
      <p class="mb-0">Learners build workplace habits through real tasks, feedback, and mentorship. Tracks run for multiple weeks with clear goals and checkpoints, and can include areas like child development, food handling, culinary basics, and community service.</p>
      <p class="mb-0"><strong>Outcomes:</strong> resume and interview readiness, professional soft skills, teamwork, and confidence earned through meaningful service and on-the-job practice.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Individual Consultation & Support -->
  <div class="card mb-5 p-4 border-green">
    <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-4">
      <h4 class="mb-0">Individual Consultation & Support</h4>
      <p class="lead mb-0">Personalized guidance rooted in Relationship Development Intervention (RDI). We begin with strengths and build trusted routines that support everyday communication and self-regulation.</p>
      <p class="mb-0">Plans are flexible and responsive, blending in-person and virtual support to fit real life. Goals evolve through ongoing observation, reflection, and collaboration with families.</p>
      <p class="mb-0"><strong>Outcomes:</strong> greater self-awareness, practical regulation strategies, and clear communication patterns that transfer across home, school, and community settings.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Professional Development -->
  <div class="card mb-5 p-4 border-yellow">
    <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-4">
      <h4 class="mb-0">Professional Development</h4>
      <p class="lead mb-0">Collaborative training that strengthens the entire learning ecosystem. Sessions equip educators, caregivers, and professionals with research-based practices and a strengths-focused lens.</p>
      <p class="mb-0">Formats range from concise workshops to multi-session series, all designed to translate current research into practical strategies for inclusive, relationship-centered environments.</p>
      <p class="mb-0"><strong>Outcomes:</strong> clearer understanding of neurodiversity, actionable tools for everyday practice, and a shared language that builds supportive communities.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>












